  "body": "I've got a component that renders the following:\n\n```\nrender () {\n    <div>\n        <form onSubmit={this.onAdd.bind(this)}>\n          <input type='text' />\n          <input type='submit' value='Add' />\n        </form>\n      </div>\n}\n```\n\nWhen I mount the same root component with different props on the previously rendered node I receive the error `Uncaught Error: Invariant Violation: Component (with keys: getDOMNode,_handleChange,props,context,state,refs,_reactInternalInstance) contains`render`method but is not mounted in the DOM`.\n\nNow, If i remove both inputs from the form above the error goes away.\n\nAn important note is that I'm using contexts and the component above lives inside `this.context.activePanel` in the root.\n\nEven though there's an error everything works as expected.\n",
